  "text": "• Menopause: One of the most common reported somatic symptoms is paresthesia in the extremities [CITATION_1] . Decreasing estrogen production causes decreased structural effectiveness of collagen and thinning of the skin. This leads to reduced blow flow to the superficial nerves and symptoms of numbness and tingling [CITATION_2] .",
